      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, we've got a problem. The candidate just told me they're officially backing the new Tax Act, even though they spent the last month trashing it in every interview. The press is already circling. If this looks like a total flip-flop, our consistency score is going to tank and we'll lose the swing voters. How do we handle the reporter's question about the sudden change in position without making it look like he's just shifting for political gain?",
